The disciplinary committee of Inter Party Advisory Council (IPAC) in Bayelsa State has called for the suspension of its Deputy Chairman, Mr Alex Peretu, Secretary, Mr Henry Ebikibena and four others over “unauthorised audience” with the Governor of Bayelsa State, Senator Douye Diri. Other leaders of the body that are facing possible suspension include; Barr. Nabai Alfred, Legal Adviser; Mr Ebimobowei Sikpi, Financial Secretary; Mr Fayefori Bobmanuel, Youth Policy Adviser; and Mr William Paleowei, representative of persons living with disability. According to a statement signed by the state chairman, Hon. James Inengite and secretary of the disciplinary committee, Azibafaram Cameroon.